reviewText: Even though my daughter loves to TALK like George :| you can't beat the fun stories, lessons learned, and ideas on ways you can take and run with the things that George learns (and the children after each episode explore) to enhance your child's learning.  We have an embarrassingly large library of Curious George DVD's, but the stories have really been a great jumping off point for us in getting our four-year-old interested in learning different things. Go, George!!
Title: Curious George: Goes to a Birthday Party

reviewText: This is a delightful collection of birthday parties that Curious George attends, including one for the adult Quints.  Clever and touching stories.  Good for children of all ages.
summary: Curious George Goes to a Birthday Party
Title: Curious George: Goes to a Birthday Party

reviewText: My child is a big Curious George fan.  He has really enjoyed this DVD and has watched it numerous times.
Title: Curious George: Goes to a Birthday Party

reviewText: I purchased this DVD for my 4 year old son.  He absolutely LOVES Curious George so naturally it has been a great gift.  I found that Curious George is teaching my son a few very interesting things about nature and animals too.  It has been almost 20 years since I was in school so I also find myself learning a few things too which is fun and exciting.  Curious George is always a great conversation anytime with my son! FOUR THUMBS UP!!!!
summary: Curious George For Curious Little Boy

reviewText: My 3 year old is on a Curious George kick! Since his birthday, last month, he has been into watching anything birthday related! This DVD has two episodes of a birthday party on it. It keeps his attention and he has learned some funny things from watching these DVDs. One thing he says a lot is, "it's for babies!" He cracks us up!
